        </div>

        <div class="questions">
          <p>
            When your stove works but the oven breaks, there could be several
            reasons behind this issue:
          </p>
          <p>
            <b> Gas Supply Issue:</b> If you have a gas oven, but the stove (which
            typically operates on gas) works fine while the oven does not, there
            might be an issue with the gas supply specifically to the oven. This
            could be due to a malfunctioning gas valve or a blockage in the oven's
            supply line.
          </p>

          <p>
            <b>Igniter Problems:</b>Gas ovens use an igniter to ignite the gas
            and create the flame necessary for heating. If the oven igniter is
            faulty or not working correctly, it can prevent the oven from
            heating up while allowing the stove burners to function normally.
          </p>

          <p>
            <b>Thermostat Malfunction:</b>The oven thermostat regulates the
            temperature by controlling the flow of gas or electricity to the
            heating elements. If the thermostat is defective or out of
            calibration, it may not signal the oven to heat up properly even
            though the stove burners work fine.
          </p>

          <p>
            <b>Faulty Heating Element:</b>Electric ovens rely on these to
            generate heat. If one or more of these elements is faulty or burned
            out, it can prevent the oven from heating while the stove continues
            to operate normally.
          </p>

          <p>
            <b>Control Panel Malfunctions:</b>The control board serves as the
            "brain" of the oven, governing its various functions and settings.
            If the control board is malfunctioning or has failed, it may not
            send the necessary signals to the oven components to initiate the
            heating process.
          </p>

          <p>
            <b>Wiring Problems:</b>An electric oven requires proper wiring to
            supply power to the heating elements and other components. If there
